s on tho sofa and reads the\npiper.\"\nThis type of case is far from now to tho staff at tho\nChildren's Cantor. If tho parents will accept counseling\nthemselves, Frank can be helped.\nIn this type of case sometimes parents would rather\ntake their son to tho clinic than to a reform school, and\nthen remain aloof.\n\"Wo can't maka progress than,\" Alaxandar B. Campbell,\nacting diractor of tho Cantor, said. \"These era exactly the\nkinds of parents who need assistance the most.\"\ne e\nStar of Movies\u2014\n(Continuad from Pago 1)\nTHE CHRIST. \"SECOND COMIN6,\" CONTRIBUTES\nTHE MARVELOUS REVELATION THAT DEVIL. HELL,\n\"MATTER,\" SIN, DISEASE, DEATH, WARS EVEN,\nARE ALL U-N-R-E*A-L 111\nHUMAN AND \"MATERIAL.\" OBJECTS ARE MERELY\nVISIBLE, M-Y-T-H-l-C-A-L, MORTAL T-W-O-U-C-H T\nIMAGES, COUNTERFEITS, AND BURLESQUES OF\nDIVINE IDEAS I\nStar af Mevitt In \u20189os.\nHolon Twakratraas, DoaJ\n(Tlmot)\nMIDDLETOWN, Pfc, Fob. U (INS)\u2014Formor tf*9o and\nKroon Mar Holon Twataatraaa EM yaafarday at Mm Ohm\nataad Air Forco Bom HoapHat.\nIN. Thomat J. Prltdmy, DAUPHIN COUNTY CORONER,\naaM May an aufayay Anmk MISS TWELVSTREES, 4*\nMIO OF AN OVERDOSE Os DRUBS.\n(Canflnuad IM Column T\u00aby)\nAPPARINTLY SHI HAD tH OttAT FAIN FOR\nSOMC TIMI FROM A KIDNEY AUMRNT, I* uk\u00a3 Niw|\n''lt t possible that Mite TiiUilWM t<4\n\nf\nICTCHtAIRBT SPtftKS lOR THE DEVIL I-\nS. Oitman, UCtA (MycWa*rf\u00abfe TMa Mt< a\ndrug Rut integrate* man with raality, imprevas hi* bshsvior\nand raducas hK, all-too-f raquant impultlvanesa\u2014a raaponti*\nyilty pHL'\" (Fraa Free*, 3/20)\nTRULY I GOD'S CHRIST SUPfiR SCIINCE ALONE\nCOMPETENT TO FULFILL SAME I\n\"THE ROAD TO HELL IS PAVED WITH GOOD\nINTENTIONS\"\nGOD. ADDITIONALLY. TO HIS DETROIT TRMMJNI:\nDRUGS AND PILLS ARE INVOLUNTARY FRAUDS*\u2014\n'THE FLESH PROFITETH NOTHING. IT IS THE SPIRIT\nTHAT QUICKENETN. THE. WORDS THAT I SPEAK\nUNTO YOU. THEY ARE SPIRIT AND THEY ARE LIFE\" I\n\u2014Jaews in John 6:63.\nEVERY EFFECT IS A MENTAL PHENOMENON!\nTHE UNIVERSE IS 100% THE MANIFESTATION OF\nTHOUGHT I 1\nMARVELOUS CHRIST SCIENCE MESSIAH\nIMPERATIVE TO APPREHEND M-A-U-T-Y\nBUT, A \"DECLARATION OF INDEPENDENCE\"\nIMPERATIVE I\nFROM THE M-Y-T-H-I-C-AL, DEVILISH. ANTI\nCHRIST. ADAM-EVE, MURDEROUS CAIN, JUDAS.\nKNAVES AND FOOLS' EGO AND PSYCHOLOGY\nOF ALL HUMAN BIRTHS t \"THE GHASTLY FARCE\nOF MATERIAL fso-callad] EXISTENCE\" I\n\u2014p. 272. SAH.\nSAYS CHORES WOULD CURB DELINQUENCY\n(N. Y. Tribuna, 3/1)\nJuvenile delinquency might not be increasing at the\npresent alarming pace if youths today wara subjected to\nstiffer parental discipline and had a few more household\nchores to do. United States Attorney Paul W. Williams sug\ngested yesterday.\n\"In these days when the household chore has all but\ndisappeared.\" ha said, \"many of our children era taught tp\nlead a soft life of frustrating idleness.\" The result, ha indi\ncated. is that normal urges for achievement and adventure\nmay than be channeled away from constructive goats and\ninto delinquent conduct.\n\nAN ACCURATE OBSERVATION ON HEBREWS,\nNOT YET HAVING BECOME SPIRITUAL 'JEWS/\nCHRISTIIKE CHRISTIAN SCIENTISTS,\nMY CHOSEN PEOPLE I\nLET'S EXPLORE YOUR MIND J T\u00a3Vi XO\n2. Telling Jokes on Yourself Incffcates a Great\nSence of Humor.\n(A Cover Up)\nTrue False (Free Press. 6/27)\n2. False, says psychiatrist Thedor Relk. In his outstand\ning study of the jokes that Jaws tall on themselvee ho con\ncludes that these are based upon doapsoatod hostilities. In\ndepreciating himsalf, the Jaw Is really portraying the\nviciousnass of Gentilo discrimination. Ho is alto exproesing\nsorious doubts about a God who will allow such things te\nhappen. The views here stated ere those of Dr. Reik. not\nours.\n\n\"CAN A PERSON BE\nSAVED BY HIS MOTHER'S PRAYERS?\"\n\u2014asked of Rev. Billy Graham.\n(Fraa Prat)\nQUESTION: Can a per:on b: saved by his mother's\nprayers? L. I. L.\nANSWER: A man who hos a praying mother hot o most\ncherished possession. I can think of no greater her it ego\nthen that of a saintly, praying mother. I have thanked God\nover and over again for a Christian mother.\nHowever, though mother's prayers may greatly Influence\na man's life end invoke the mercy of God on his behalf, if\ncould hardly be said that a parson can be saved by mother's\nprayers.\nOur decision for Christ is one that wo must moke our\nselves. Your mother's faithful prayers may have a great\naffect on you, but the ultimata and final decision It up to\nyou. This is said with no intent of minimising tho value\nand affactivanass of faithful, praying parent*.\n\nUPRISING FACES SOVIET, EX-RED\nTELLS MANION\n(Chicago Tribune, 2/17)\nClarence Men ion, former dean of law at the University\nOs Notre Dome, interviewed Nickoiei Khokhlov, former cap*\ntain of intelligence in the soviet army, In, his weekly tedlOi\nprogram last night over station W-G-M and the Mutual\nBroadcasting system network.\nKhokhlov predicted that theca will be an anti-communist\nrevolution in Russia, \"some time in IRRf ee TP6O.\" He \u00bbeld\nthat a \"spiritual revolution\" already hat started In the Soviet\nUnion end that e new tendency \"te demand finally that\nfreedom be granted\" is rising there.\nIChekhlev said he was born in Russia In IflS end was a\nranniiimtst until 1f54, when he wet drafted into soviet\ninttlvigpncD.\nI got to the conclusion that communism to wrong end\niXit EX'\"\n4 \u00abah\n\u2022l i tv,","height":"28044","width":"18609"}}
